%e A327854 1.87840(9) * 10^(-29) h^2 g cm^(-3), where h = 0.678(9) is a dimensionless scale factor (cf. Aldrovandi et al., 2002, p. 4) for the present day Hubble expansion rate H_0, which equals 100*h km s^(-1) Mpc^(-1) and where the digit in parentheses denotes the standard uncertainty (cf. Tanabashi et al., 2018, table 2.1).
